[[Image:Ben Knapen 2012.jpg|thumb|right|220px|Ben Knapen]]
'''Hubertus Petrus Maria "Ben" Knapen''' (born 6 January 1951 in [[Kaatsheuvel]]) is a [[Netherlands|Dutch]] politician of the [[Christian Democratic Appeal]] (CDA). Since 9 June 2015, he has been a member of the [[Senate (Netherlands)|Senate]].
==Career== Knapen was the [[State Secretary (Netherlands)|State Secretary]] for [[Ministry of Foreign Affairs (Netherlands)|Foreign Affairs]] in the [[first Rutte cabinet]], serving from 14 October 2010 to 5 November 2012. His portfolio comprised [[European Union]] matters, as well as [[international aid]].<ref>{{nl icon}} [http://www.cda.nl/Onze_mensen/Per_organisatie/Kabinet/Onze_mensen/Ben_Knapen.aspx Ben Knapen] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101229105940/http://www.cda.nl/Onze_mensen/Per_organisatie/Kabinet/Onze_mensen/Ben_Knapen.aspx |date=December 29, 2010 }} ''[[Christian Democratic Appeal]]''</ref> Today, he is on the advisory board of OMFIF where he is regularly involved in meetings regarding the financial and monetary system.
==Other activities== * [[African Development Bank]] (AfDB), Ex-Officio Member of the Board of Governors (2010-2012)<ref>[https://www.afdb.org/fileadmin/uploads/afdb/Documents/Publications/Annual%20Report%202010%20EN.pdf AfDB Annual Report 2010] [[African Development Bank]] (AfDB).</ref>
