{{Infobox Organization |name = Federation of Businesses of the Congo |image = |image_border = |size = |caption = |map = |msize = |mcaption = |motto = |formation = 1997 |extinction = |type = Employer federation |headquarters = 10 Avenue des aviateurs |location = [[Gombe, Kinshasa|Gombe]], [[Kinshasa]], [[Democratic Republic of the Congo]] |membership = |language = |leader_title = President |leader_name = [[Albert Yuma Mulimbi]] |key_people = |num_staff = |budget = |website = [http://www.fec-rdc.com/ fec-rdc.com] }} The '''Federation of Businesses of the Congo''' ({{lang-fr|Fédération des entreprises du Congo}}) is the main [[employers' organization]] in the [[Democratic Republic of the Congo]]. Established in 1997, it had 2, 700 members in 2010.<ref name="jeuneafriquelepatrondespatrons">{{cite news|last1=Meunier|first1=Marianne|title=Albert Yuma Mulimbi, le patron des patrons|url=http://www.jeuneafrique.com/197166/archives-thematique/albert-yuma-mulimbi-le-patron-des-patrons/|accessdate=December 24, 2016|work=Jeune Afrique|date=May 12, 2010}}</ref> It received financial support from the [[French Development Agency]] in 2010.<ref name="frenchdevappui">{{cite web|title=Appui à la Fédération des Entreprises du Congo|url=http://www.afd.fr/home/pays/afrique/geo-afr/republique-democratique-du-congo/projets-rdc/secteur-productif-financier/appui-federation-entreprises-congo|website=French Development Agency|accessdate=December 24, 2016}}</ref> Its president is [[Albert Yuma Mulimbi]].<ref name="jeuneafriquelepatrondespatrons"/>
